This should be a good spot. Now, show yourself.\n< Serena >
Ah... uhh... Serena... san?\n< ?? >

Ah, as I thought... that voice... it's a pleasant
sound that resonates in my heart...\n< Serena >
It was you, Lord Tim.\n< Serena >

This feeling... ah... Serena-san... I'm so glad...
you're alive... truly glad...\n< Tim >

So it was indeed you, Lord Tim, who carried me out
of the city to a safe place.\n< Serena >
Thanks to you, I am still alive.\n< Serena >

And you also tried to save me from Gibier by
sending the black slime.\n< Serena >
I am grateful...\n< Serena >

No, perhaps this is the more appropriate way to
say it at a time like this.\n< Serena >
Thank you, Lord Tim.\n< Serena >

This feeling... I thought it must be conveyed
directly.\n< Serena >

Heh heh... Serena-san is very earnest... but I
like you just the way you are...\n< Tim >
Ugh...\n< Tim >
AudioManager.playSe({"name":"Darkness1","volume":100,"pitch":100,"pan":0})

Ah! Guh... my consciousness is fading... if this
continues... something worse will happen...\n< Tim >
Serena-san... I have one last request...\n< Tim >
Please... kill me...\n< Tim >
...\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

Forgive me, Splendor. Could you lend me my body
back just for this moment?\n< Serena >

I want to face him in the form that I spent time
with Lord Tim.\n< Serena >
...!\n< Serena >

Ah... aaaaah... Splendor. My radiance... I am
thankful...\n< Serena >
...!\n< Serena >

Prepare yourself... spawn of evil that taints this
world...\n< Serena >
Serena Fuoco Ril Brilante di la Grazia...\n< Serena >
No...\n< Serena >
It's Serena... I will save Lord Tim!\n< Serena >

I've caught it... your sound.\n< Serena >
Ma-ma-ma...\n< ?? >
Haaaah...!\n< Serena >

It took some effort due to your soft body... but
as long as you have a physical form, there is
sound within you. Waves. Rhythms.\n< Serena >

I've captured that sound and "dressed you" in
Apherbile.\n< Serena >

You are enveloped in an armor of sound.
Resonating, reverberating, the bouncing sound
becomes billions of vibrations.\n< Serena >
And vibration is, in essence, heat.\n< Serena >
Ghh...!\n< Serena >
Ouch...!\n< Serena >
Heh...!\n< Serena >
My heat...\n< Serena >
Into my Phorcys!\n< Serena >
Burn!\n< Serena >
Be exhausted!\n< Serena >
Ma-ma.\n< ?? >
What...?\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

Pururururu...
Oh... ohh...\n< Serena >
Splendor...\n< Serena >
My radiance...\n< Serena >

Splendor, as long as you're safe, that's all that
matters... I am...\n< Serena >
Bururu...
Burururu! Hihiiin!
Hey!\n< Cecilia >
Don't mess with me! Just now, with its horn...!\n< Cecilia >
...\n< Serena >
It's alright, Lady Cecilia.\n< Serena >
Nothing's alright!\n< Cecilia >

It can't be helped... it's in its nature. Splendor
has done nothing wrong.\n< Serena >

All the evil lies within me. This creature is
merely reacting to that ugliness.\n< Serena >
...\n< Cecilia >
...Splendor. I'm sorry for causing you discomfort.\n< Serena >

Just sleep a little longer... I'll take you home
soon...\n< Serena >
Bur... Bururu... Hi... Hiiin...

...Phew.\n< Serena >
Ouch... now that I've calmed down, the pain is...\n< Serena >

This is... I might not be able to play the piano
anymore. I've just given my father and mother
another reason to scold me.\n< Serena >
...Serena.\n< Cecilia >

So, Serena, what was all this for...? What did you
work so hard for? This is...\n< Cecilia >
It's just too much...\n< Cecilia >
...I didn't do all this expecting any reward.\n< Serena >

I simply wanted to repay a friendship. Even if
it's something that has long passed.\n< Serena >

I made a decision and followed through with it...
that's why I'm satisfied.\n< Serena >
...I'm satisfied.\n< Serena >
Bururu...
Burururu! Hiiin!

Ah... Splendor...! The white fur on your back that
I've dreamed of...!\n< Serena >
I won't let go...! Not ever again...!\n< Serena >

...Ha... I don't really understand what's going
on, but anyway, the operation was a success... Is
this really okay?\n< Cecilia >

The fortress seems to be in total chaos. They're
not in any position to bother us anymore. Let's
slip away unnoticed.\n< Cecilia >
But seriously, what was that thing earlier?\n< Cecilia >

I saw it once before in the sewers... A black
slime. No... perhaps it wasn't slime.\n< Serena >

Lady Katarine mentioned it. Beneath this city, the
lingering thoughts of numerous unborn children
remain. Those thoughts gather and form a curse...\n< Serena >

That might have been the curse itself. Why it
appeared here and now, I do not know...\n< Serena >

...Come to think of it, Lady Katarine did ask me
to show them understanding...\n< Serena >

What is that woman talking about? It's not like
we're strangers.\n< Cecilia >

Serena has no obligation to deal with such things.
I blew it away! Serves them right!\n< Cecilia >

You don't need to worry about that story either,
Serena. Don't let it dampen our happy ending.\n< Cecilia >

That's true... I'm sorry, but all I could do was
save this child.\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

Let's go home, Splendor. Father and Mother are
surely very angry.\n< Serena >
I might end up crying when they scold me.\n< Serena >
If that happens, please comfort me again...\n< Serena >

Ugh!!!\n< Serena >
This, monster...!?\n< Serena >
Serena!\n< Cecilia >
Lady Cecilia! Don't worry about me!\n< Serena >

It seems this monster is after me... Take Splend-r
and run...!\n< Serena >
Aguh...!\n< Serena >
...!\n< Serena >
...I'm sorry. I'm so sorry!\n< Cecilia >
...\n< Serena >

So this is... the end... to die in a place like
this...\n< Serena >
It's more anticlimactic than I thought.\n< Serena >
But well, at least Splend-r is safe.\n< Serena >

Though I won't get to hold that child in my arms
again,\n< Serena >
I'm half satisfied.\n< Serena >
Half is...\n< Serena >

Is it... impossible for me...\n< Serena >
...Is something still missing?\n< Serena >

Ugh!?\n< Serena >
Nice catch!!!\n< ??? >

Man, with this, I could totally make a southpaw
debut!\n< ??? >
Hmph, such an optimistic way of speaking.\n< Serena >
As ever, it's good to see you haven't changed.\n< Serena >
Lady Erika.\n< Serena >

Hello. Seems like you're in a bind! Big sis has
come to the rescue.\n< Erika >
Ouch, ouch, ouch----!! My wounds... my wounds...\n< Erika >

Argh... sorry. Looks like I can't join in on such
a flashy battle after all.\n< Erika >
But this should be useful to you!\n< Erika >
Hm? A grenade...?\n< Serena >
No, that's not it! This is...\n< Serena >
AudioManager.playSe({"name":"Magic1","volume":100,"pitch":100,"pan":0})
The Brilliante family heirloom!\n< Serena >
Lady Erika! Where on earth did you find this!\n< Serena >

An old acquaintance, a wizard, came to visit me.
He brought it saying it was a rare item.\n< Erika >

I thought it sounded familiar, and sure enough, it
seemed related to you, Serena-chan!\n< Erika >

I've been wanting to hand it over quickly, so
that's why I came here!\n< Erika >
As expected of you, Lady Erika...\n< Serena >
But.\n< Serena >
I am grateful.\n< Serena >

Then I'll go scatter the guys coming this way so
they don't interrupt!\n< Erika >

I always seem to be in your debt...\n< Serena >
Thank you. My friend, Lady Erika.\n< Serena >
The Brilliante family heirloom...\n< Serena >

To think it would return to me like this, after
all this time and even as I've changed in
appearance.\n< Serena >
Ah, I can feel it. The power. The power of Grazia.\n< Serena >

...Let us march forth, Lord Tim! This time for
sure... with this power...!\n< Serena >

$gameScreen.showPicture(7,"PC007-01/復活カット2",0,0,0,100,100,255,0)
Ah... Serena-san, thank you... with this...\n< Tim >
No, not yet. Lord Tim. I shall...!\n< Serena >

But I... I've already committed so many sins, I'm
tainted... my hands are already pitch black...\n< Tim >

I too have sinned... but I am still alive. Sins
are not something to be erased... they are to be
atoned for!\n< Serena >
That's why... that's why!!\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >

Serena-san...? What are you doing by removing your
armor...?\n< Tim >

...I apologize. It seems I cannot return you to
your original form...\n< Serena >

However, the filth you've shouldered... the
darkness gnawing at your soul, I will take it upon
myself.\n< Serena >
Someday, I will erase all the filth,\n< Serena >
and I will save your soul, Lord Tim.\n< Serena >

But as I am now, it's no good. This is a cage to
protect me.\n< Serena >

Therefore, I will reconstruct the magic power...
the Afa-Bile into a suitable form.\n< Serena >

Not a cage to protect me, but a cradle to heal
you.\n< Serena >
Serena-san...\n< Tim >

Oh treasure of the Brillante family, my radiance!
If I am still worthy of it now...\n< Serena >
AudioManager.playSe({"name":"Magic1","volume":100,"pitch":100,"pan":0})
Grant me strength! The power to save him!\n< Serena >

And... Splendour... my brilliance! If you forgive
me...\n< Serena >

Grant me strength! The power to heal him!\n< Serena >

It's fine if my magic power is exhausted... even
if it means I can't return to my original form.\n< Serena >

So... you two miracles that represent me! Even if
just for a moment...\n< Serena >
Grant me... the power to save...\n< Serena >
The power to save Lord Tim!!\n< Serena >
Ah... Serena-san!\n< Tim >

Can you hear it... Lord Tim. The sound of my
heart.\n< Serena >
Ah... this is... Serena-san's... heartbeat...\n< Tim >

Yes. My heartbeat... amplified by the Afa-Bile
with the sound of my feelings.\n< Serena >

And the many layers of sound are woven into a
lullaby that lulls you to sleep...\n< Serena >

I can hear it, Serena-san's song. I can feel it,
Serena-san's warmth.\n< Tim >
AudioManager.playSe({"name":"Ice4","volume":100,"pitch":100,"pan":0})

Now, Lord Tim, it's time for sleep. A long,
long... sleep...\n< Serena >
Wrapped in this body... sleep... within me...\n< Serena >
Tim... my lord...\n< Serena >
Ah... Sere... na... san.\n< Tim >

Serena-san... I... I am... about you, Serena-
san...\n< Tim >
...\n< Serena >
Ah, me too...\n< Serena >
...\n< Serena >
...Goodnight, Lord Tim.\n< Serena >
